Principal Deputy National Security Advisor Jon Finer recently spoke with UN Relief and Works Agency for Palestine Refugees in the Near East (UNRWA) Commissioner General Philippe Lazzarini to address the dire humanitarian situation in Gaza. Finer expressed condolences for the loss of 103 UNRWA staff, the highest number in any conflict, and appreciation for their commitment to delivering aid and services. They discussed the need to protect civilians, including UN staff and aid workers, and prevent aid diversion to Hamas. The United States remains dedicated to supporting UNRWA's crucial work in providing essential assistance to millions in Gaza. Finer emphasized the importance of enabling life-saving humanitarian aid to reach those in need.